The fermion operator  $R^\dagger$ transforms a meson state $\vert M, L  \rangle$ with orbital angular momentum $L$ into a nucleon state $ \vert N, L - 1\rangle$ with orbital $L-1$: The superpartners have the same parity. The operator $R^\dagger$ also annihilates the lowest possible mass state, the pion, which has no nucleon superpartner ~\cite{Dosch:2015nwa}:

text:
